# Project Context

NASA interplanetary fuel calculator (NEX Energy code challenge). Monorepo with npm workspaces:

- `apps/client` — Vite + React SPA
- `apps/server` — Node.js WebSocket server
- `packages/fuel-core` — pure fuel calculation logic
- `packages/shared` — types and planet constants

## Rules

- Fuel logic lives in `packages/fuel-core` only. Never duplicate formulas in client or server.
- Server is thin transport: validate input, call `fuel-core`, return results.
- Client has no calculation logic; server is the source of truth for fuel numbers.
- Real-time is required: persistent WebSocket, no manual submit button.
- Updates must fire on every input change (mass, flight steps, planet/action).

## Acceptance Values

| Mission        | Mass   | Total Fuel |
|----------------|--------|------------|
| Apollo 11      | 28,801 | 51,898     |
| Mars Mission   | 14,606 | 33,388     |
| Passenger Ship | 75,432 | 212,161    |

